Foreign and domestic disinformation campaigns also intensified. The administration leaked claims to friendly outlets that it had brokered a peace deal in Ukraine, only to have President Zelensky and Russian officials deny that any such agreement existed. Behind the scenes, a leaked transcript showed Trump envoy Steve Witkoff coordinating directly with Russian officials on a 28\uc0\u8209 point \'93peace plan\'94 drafted in Moscow, pressing Ukraine to accept territorial concessions, military limits, and amnesty for Russian war crimes. Vice President J.D. Vance praised the plan, while Secretary of State Marco Rubio tried to distance the administration from it, calling it a Russian wish list, only to be contradicted by his own department. The confusion was not accidental. It created a fog in which responsibility for policy could be denied and foreign influence obscured. At home, Tennessee\'92s secretary of state ordered 181 public libraries to review and remove books with LGBTQ themes, citing state anti\u8209 DEI law and a Trump executive order against \'93gender ideology.\'94 Libraries closed temporarily to conduct the purge. Trump again threatened to revoke ABC\'92s license over unfavorable coverage, and he publicly insulted female reporters as \'93stupid\'94 and \'93ugly.\'94 Together, these actions narrow the range of acceptable stories and voices.\
